
[1]bbarbacan

   B'BARBACAN, n.

   1. A fortification or outer defense to a city or castle, consisting of
   an elevation of earth about three feet high, along the foot of the
   rampart.

   2. A fortress at the end of a bridge, or at the outlet of a city,
   having a double wall with towers.

   3. An opening in the wall of a fortress through which guns are leveled
   and fired upon an enemy.

     The French use the word also for an aperture in a wall to let in or
   drain off water; and the Spaniards, for a low wall round a church yard.
     __________________________________________________________________

